ArcelorMittal May Build $1 Billion Brazil Plant, Reuters Says

-- B y   P e t e r   M i l l a r d
-- 
2011-06-02T12:45:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/arcelormittal-may-build-1-billion-brazil-plant-reuters-says.html
ArcelorMittal (MT) , the world’s biggest
steelmaker, may build a $1 billion steel laminate plant at its
Tubarao steel mill in  Brazil , Benjamin Baptista Filho, the head
of the company’s Brazil operations, told  Reuters  in an
interview.  ArcelorMittal should approve the project before the end of
2012, Reuters reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Millard in Rio de Janeiro at 
 Pmillard1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  